@DeathOfJack hey what you should try is to delete every thing in side this folder: YOUR COMPUTER NAME/Library/aplication support/minecraft EXEPT SAVES so you delete the bin folder resources etc. then drag and drop the saves out that folder (if you wanna keep your saves if not, just delete all) now you have a folder downloaded called "minecraft" this represents the folder from application support... open both up and drag and drop all the content (the folders...) from the downloaded minecraft to the minecraft you already had IF YOU DIDN"T HAVE A MINECRAFT FOLDER JUST DRAG AND DROP THE WHOLE DOWNLOADED MINECRAFT FOLDER IN APPLICATION SUPPORT now go back to minecraft auto updater 1.7.3 auto updater and drag and drop the minecraft icon to your applications

you see a folder called mods -you don't need those- they are just extra mods for peeps who know how to install them....

